profile_positions.description:
•	Build Project Management maturity at the organizational level;
•	Assist project teams in all phases of their projects from project initiation to project closure 
•	Train organizational Project Managers in a full range of Project Management topics if necessary or requested e.g., Unisys Associated Project Manager 
•	Serve as honest broker on all issues brought forward to the PMO by Project Managers
•	Advise and assists in the Quality and timeliness of project planning documents;
•	Defined and maintained the standards of process,  related to project management, within the organization;
•	Standardize and introduce economies of repetition in the execution of projects; 
•	Operational and tactical support of the establishment, implementation and monitoring of projects;
•	Maintained a source of documentation, guidance and metrics on the practice of project management and execution;
•	Governed the management of projects; 
•	Introduced project management principles on industry-standard methodologies such as IPMA and  PRINCE2; 
•	Influential and participating in industry certification programs such as ISO9001-1994 en 2000; 
•	People Manager for both the PMO and the Proposal Center; 
•	Responsible for the execution of internal projects audits;
•	Safeguarding and implementing the Unisys internal Teammethod Project Management methodology; 
•	Responsible for Project Status Reviews Submission Guidelines and Policy;
•	Review all proposals on do-ability of the planning, budget and other financials and risk exposure; 
•	Review of projects on status of risk, progress, quality and financials; 
•	Quality Manager function.

Product Manager and Business Process Consultant for the European Business Process Solutions Program
•	Responsible for all by Unisys Corporation developed Business Process products in the areas of Document, Imaging en Workflow Management in Continental Europe and UK;
•	Presales, demonstrations, client discussion sessions; 
•	Assist pursuit team with their proposals and sales; approach;assist in writing architectures and solutions;
•	Demonstrate and present to clients and Unisys internal on  capabilities of the solutions;
•	Implemented solutions / projects with the local teams; 
•	Acted as european support representative on application and technical issues;
•	Presented on numerous trade shows;
•	Representative on future developments board.
